The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Wednesday, June 25, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Wednesday, June 25, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on the AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses and minibuses heading towards Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																Debate				 																																	A discussion on Kamasutra  Sex education manual or taboo text for teens?, with Konkona Sen Sharma, Kiran Uttam Ghosh, Dr Rima Mukherjee, Meera Kakkar, Rahul Singh and Komal Kalha at Oxford Bookstore, 7 pm.				 																Paintings				 																																	An exhibition by Bikramjit Roy of traditional Mysore -style paintings embossed with gold foil at Academy of Fine Arts, 3 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	Summer Interlude, a show of paintings by several painters, organised by Artists Circle at 46, Circus Avenue.				 																																	Summer Show of Affordable Heritage, an exhibition of paintings by masters of the last century, at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 4 pm to 8 pm.				 																Posters				 																																	An exhibition of prints and posters of European and Indian masters, entitled Prints Posters and Beyond, at Vikalp Art Shop, Swabhumi, 4 pm to 8 pm.				 																Mime				 																																	A mime show by ventriloquist Goutam Adhikary at Swabhumi, 6 pm.
